Question: What is the primary role of an Operating System?

A) Managing hardware resources
B) Executing application programs
C) Providing user interfaces
D) All of the above
Answer: D) All of the above
Question: Which of the following is not a state of a process in Linux?

A) TASK_RUNNING (R)
B) TASK_PAUSED (P)
C) TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE (D)
D) TASK_ZOMBIE (Z)
Answer: B) TASK_PAUSED (P)
Question: What does a super block (Volume Control Block) contain?

A) Information about CPU scheduling
B) Information about file system capacity and label
C) Information about process execution
D) Information about network connections
Answer: B) Information about file system capacity and label
Question: Which command is used to format a partition with ext3 file system in Linux?

A) mkfs -t ext3 /dev/sdb1
B) format /dev/sdb1 ext3
C) fsck -t ext3 /dev/sdb1
D) mount -t ext3 /dev/sdb1
Answer: A) mkfs -t ext3 /dev/sdb1
Question: What is the function of the inode in UNIX/Linux file systems?

A) Stores file contents
B) Stores file metadata
C) Manages disk partitions
D) Handles CPU scheduling
Answer: B) Stores file metadata


